497
00:31:22,927 --> 00:31:24,784
Quincy, keep an eye on things.

498
00:31:25,377 --> 00:31:26,480
Right, boss.

499
00:31:30,485 --> 00:31:31,552
It’s grandma!

500
00:31:31,967 --> 00:31:33,734
She’s supposed to be missing.

501
00:31:33,877 --> 00:31:36,155
Ah, this ruins everything.

502
00:31:36,341 --> 00:31:41,005
Mr. Bucks will call off the deal.
There goes your fortune and my 50 percent.

503
00:31:41,348 --> 00:31:44,230
– Ten percent.
– Thirty percent! Plus expenses.

504
00:31:44,818 --> 00:31:45,589
Done.

505
00:31:47,878 --> 00:31:49,138
I’ve got an idea.

506
00:31:49,613 --> 00:31:52,190
You just make sure grandma stays missing.

507
00:32:10,323 --> 00:32:11,702
Hey! Hey! Come back!

508
00:32:15,533 --> 00:32:17,434
Grandma Spankenheimer?

509
00:32:17,695 --> 00:32:21,272
Yes, they sent me down to get you.
Now, if you’ll just follow me?

510
00:32:21,513 --> 00:32:22,624
Sure, sweetie.

511
00:32:22,932 --> 00:32:25,818
Say, you wouldn’t happen to have any antacid?

512
00:32:29,701 --> 00:32:30,425
Wait!

513
00:32:31,018 --> 00:32:34,021
Mr. Bucks, you can’t buy the store
from cousin Mel.

514
00:32:34,551 --> 00:32:36,014
It’s not hers to sell.

515
00:32:36,385 --> 00:32:37,599
I found grandma.

516
00:32:37,788 --> 00:32:39,397
She’s waiting downstairs.

517
00:32:39,567 --> 00:32:41,488
Santa will explain everything.

518
00:32:46,740 --> 00:32:47,515
Sorry.

519
00:32:47,665 --> 00:32:49,701
Used to chimneys, not stairs.

520
00:32:49,776 --> 00:32:51,542
Fill them in while I get grandma.

521
00:32:52,492 --> 00:32:54,990
And, uh, you would be?

522
00:32:55,156 --> 00:32:56,235
Santa Claus.

523
00:33:00,493 --> 00:33:02,821
