629
00:38:55,254 --> 00:38:58,467
The jury is about to find your friend
in the red suit guilty.

630
00:38:59,100 --> 00:39:00,448
And who would that be?

631
00:39:00,468 --> 00:39:03,077
You still don’t remember a thing, do you?

632
00:39:08,350 --> 00:39:09,951
My plan is going to work.

633
00:39:10,061 --> 00:39:14,052
I’m going to be wealthy
and there’s no one who can stop me.

634
00:39:14,582 --> 00:39:16,254
Hello, inside!

635
00:39:16,491 --> 00:39:18,222
Who can that be way out here?

636
00:39:18,479 --> 00:39:21,029
How should I know?
I don’t even know who I am.

637
00:39:21,380 --> 00:39:25,236
If that’s your car parked down by the road
you better check it out.

638
00:39:25,383 --> 00:39:27,553
Some bears are hanging around it.

639
00:39:27,628 --> 00:39:29,889
Thank you! I was leaving anyway!

640
00:39:31,118 --> 00:39:33,117
Okay, but don’t take too long.

641
00:39:33,358 --> 00:39:35,094
Have a safe, fire-free day.

642
00:39:50,528 --> 00:39:51,469
Good job!

643
00:39:51,698 --> 00:39:54,512
I came as soon as I received your e-mail,
Master Jake.

644
00:39:54,864 --> 00:39:57,717
Now what do you have up your sleeve
to get me inside?

645
00:40:09,308 --> 00:40:10,522
Nice entrance!

646
00:40:10,945 --> 00:40:13,794
What’s your name again?
– Jake Spankenheimer.

647
00:40:13,885 --> 00:40:15,055
Your grandson.

648
00:40:15,850 --> 00:40:18,854
Doesn’t ring a bell but thanks, anyway.

649
00:40:19,079 --> 00:40:21,530
Don’t thank me, thank Doofus.

650
00:40:23,676 --> 00:40:27,375
And I suppose this overexcited
pooch is Doofus.

651
00:40:34,213 --> 00:40:38,213
Grandma, I don’t have a lot of time
to explain but we’re going to the store.

652
00:40:38,480 --> 00:40:39,899
What’s at the store?

653
00:40:40,057 --> 00:40:41,081
Your memory.

654
00:40:44,258 --> 00:40:46,650
This is Spankenheimer’s, remember?

655
00:40:47,452 --> 00:40:48,701
Your elf costume?

656
00:40:48,970 --> 00:40:52,480
You’d wear it to read to the kids
while their parents were shopping.

657
00:40:52,527 --> 00:40:54,164
I can’t believe it.

658
00:40:54,294 --> 00:40:55,373
You remember!

659
00:40:55,752 --> 00:40:58,410
No, that I would wear that shade of green
with my coloring.

660
00:40:58,508 --> 00:40:59,896
Easy for you to say.

661
00:41:00,718 --> 00:41:02,927
Tell me again why I’m baking two cakes?

662
00:41:03,014 --> 00:41:04,647
One’s with your recipe,

663
00:41:04,778 --> 00:41:08,563
the other uses the stuff in the vial
I found at cousin Mel’s cabin.

664
00:41:08,587 --> 00:41:10,977
And this is your famous homemade fruitcake

665
00:41:11,206 --> 00:41:13,826
that, uh, a lot of people liked.

666
00:41:24,932 --> 00:41:27,114
Jake, what am I doing here?

667
00:41:27,193 --> 00:41:29,177
Grandma, you remember!

668
00:41:31,001 --> 00:41:31,993
Oh, yeah.

669
00:41:32,657 --> 00:41:35,325
You lost your memory, but now it’s back.

670
00:41:36,886 --> 00:41:38,809
It felt like I was in a dream.

671
00:41:39,374 --> 00:41:42,927
And you were in it, and Santa Claus,
and Mrs. Claus.

672
00:41:43,738 --> 00:41:46,631
I thought I was in a …, only it was cold.

673
00:41:48,635 --> 00:41:50,836
But if everything you told me is true,

674
00:41:51,014 --> 00:41:53,307
why aren’t we at the courthouse
to prove that I’m okay?

675
00:41:54,334 --> 00:41:55,587
We’re on our way.

676
00:41:58,989 --> 00:42:00,871
Has the jury reached a verdict?

677
00:42:02,768 --> 00:42:04,385
Yes, we have, Your Honor.

678
00:42:04,582 --> 00:42:07,183
In the matter of the State v. Santa Claus

679
00:42:07,641 --> 00:42:09,605
we, the Jury, find…
– Stop!

680
00:42:10,004 --> 00:42:11,433
Santa is innocent.

681
00:42:11,472 --> 00:42:13,804
I’m grandma, and I’m not missing.

682
00:42:14,148 --> 00:42:15,306
I’m right here.

683
00:42:16,608 --> 00:42:20,027
That woman is a fraud.
Grandma doesn’t know who she is.

684
00:42:20,159 --> 00:42:22,258
Honeybunches! Grandma!

685
00:42:24,413 --> 00:42:25,753
Order in the court!

686
00:42:26,228 --> 00:42:27,907
Since grandma isn’t missing

687
00:42:28,105 --> 00:42:32,056
I hereby rule that Santa Claus is innocent
of causing her disappearance.

688
00:42:37,286 --> 00:42:38,274
Your honor,

689
00:42:38,491 --> 00:42:41,569
there are still the charges of
sleighicular hit-and-run

690
00:42:41,574 --> 00:42:43,697
and leaving the scene of an accident.

691
00:42:45,436 --> 00:42:49,621
I can answer that, Your Honor. If you
and the Jury would taste this fruitcake.

692
00:42:51,062 --> 00:42:52,296
No, don’t!

693
00:42:52,714 --> 00:42:53,920
She objects.

694
00:42:53,943 --> 00:42:55,754
Overruled. Continue.

695
00:42:56,461 --> 00:42:59,988
This one was made by grandma
using her special ingredients.

696
00:43:00,347 --> 00:43:03,950
Taste it and then compare it
to the pieces of cake

697
00:43:03,954 --> 00:43:06,291
found at the scene of the alleged crime –

698
00:43:06,433 --> 00:43:08,346
state’s evidence #12.

699
00:43:10,859 --> 00:43:12,504
Do we have to, Your Honor?

700
00:43:12,824 --> 00:43:13,966
Good question.

701
00:43:14,587 --> 00:43:15,706
Do we have to?

702
00:43:16,026 --> 00:43:18,947
Yes, I think you’ll find a difference
between the two.

703
00:43:19,433 --> 00:43:23,460
All right, in the name of justice,
we eat fruitcake.

704
00:43:30,337 --> 00:43:34,791
Now taste state’s evidence #12
found where grandma disappeared.

705
00:43:41,862 --> 00:43:43,285
So, what’s your point?

706
00:43:43,783 --> 00:43:46,748
These pieces had an extra ingredient in them

707
00:43:46,890 --> 00:43:50,572
from this vial of bad stuff found
at cousin Mel’s cabin.

708
00:43:59,230 --> 00:44:02,752
You see, Your Honor,
it had the effect of reindeer nip.

709
00:44:03,479 --> 00:44:05,996
That’s why the reindeer knocked over
grandma.

710
00:44:06,071 --> 00:44:08,103
It wasn’t Santa’s reckless driving.

711
00:44:09,184 --> 00:44:11,468
I, uh, couldn’t control myself.

712
00:44:12,429 --> 00:44:14,603
The boy has done it again.

713
00:44:15,133 --> 00:44:18,909
I rule that Santa is also innocent
of the hit-and-run charge.

714
00:44:19,071 --> 00:44:23,434
And I suppose Jake has an answer to the
charge of leaving the scene of an accident –

715
00:44:23,533 --> 00:44:25,517
sleighicular negligence?

716
00:44:25,644 --> 00:44:26,667
Doofus does.

717
00:44:26,786 --> 00:44:27,826
He’s my dog.

718
00:44:27,984 --> 00:44:29,628
What? I object.

719
00:44:30,845 --> 00:44:31,960
Let’s have it.

720
